<DOC><DOCNO> AP880317-0270 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-17-88 1454EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-OPEC     03-17 0207</FIRST><SECOND>BC-OPEC,0214</SECOND><BYLINE>OPEC President To Call Press Conference On Oil Prices</BYLINE><DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   OPEC President Rilwanu Lukman saidThursday he will announce new measures to bring stability todropping oil prices on March 22.   Lukman's two-paragraph statement did not say what the measureswould involve. The statement said the measures would be announcedat a 10:00 a.m. (4 a.m. EST) press conference and should bringstability to the volatile oil market.   On Tuesday, Lukman accused the Western press of trying todestabilize the oil market to bring down prices. He said OPEC wouldnot be stampeded into taking emergency measures to stop the fall ofoil prices.   He said the cartel would stand firm on its decision to produce15.6 million barrels of oil a day. A barrel is the equivalent of 42gallons.   Ministry sources, who declined to be identified, said Lukmanwould call an emergency OPEC meeting soon after the March 22 pressconference if consultations between members promised meaningfuldiscussion at the meeting.   The sources said price stability would be the main topic ofdiscussion if the meeting were held. A report by a private auditteam on the level of oil production among cartel members would alsobe an issue.</TEXT></DOC>